  "text": "Because XBBn (r; ; z c 1 t) << XBBn (r; ) and XBBn (r; ; z c 1 t) << XBBn (r; ) for z c 1 t > d z =2 within a finite transverse aperture, where d z is a constant, X waves can be truncated within an axially moving \"window\", If the diameter of the aperture is D, the depth of field (defined as the maximum axial distance within which the decrease of the wave magnitude is less than 6-dB with respect to their peak at the aperture surface) of the X wave Hertz potential (eqs. (20) and (21)) is given by [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] 36 ]",
